p.k: Fingers are pointed when there's a typhoid outbreak. Meanwhile, Sister Winfred considers her own prejudices after a woman gets pregnant by a married man and takes matters into her own hands. UK (2016). Cast: Jenny Agutter, Linda Bassett, Pam Ferris, Judy Parfitt, Helen George, Bryony Hannah, Laura Main, Emerald Fennell, Charlotte Ritchie, Victoria Yeates, Jack Ashton, Stephen McGann, Cliff Parisi. Director: Syd Macartney.
